Cell["\<\
With all of the points now defined, I began calculating for the torque. \
Torque is defined as the turning effort that causes an object to rotate. The \
equation for torque is known as:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992097266395308*^9, 3.9920972777812233`*^9}, {
   3.9920974531310387`*^9, 3.992097472807303*^9}, {3.992097745948107*^9, 
   3.9920981476796417`*^9}, {3.992421033765835*^9, 3.992421033879548*^9}, {
   3.992441390140338*^9, 3.9924413916989183`*^9}, {3.9925974258569527`*^9, 
   3.99259747202188*^9}, {3.992598757839549*^9, 3.99259875926333*^9}, 
   3.992601531064232*^9, {3.992615573020755*^9, 
   3.9926156081041594`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"9786bc24-135c-4404-88ac-\
fae2d8ee0e14"],

Cell["\[Tau] = F \:22c5 r \:22c5 sin(\[Phi])", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992097266395308*^9, 3.9920972777812233`*^9}, {
   3.9920974531310387`*^9, 3.992097472807303*^9}, {3.992097745948107*^9, 
   3.9920981476796417`*^9}, {3.992421033765835*^9, 3.992421033879548*^9}, {
   3.992441390140338*^9, 3.9924413916989183`*^9}, {3.9925974258569527`*^9, 
   3.99259747202188*^9}, {3.992598757839549*^9, 3.99259875926333*^9}, 
   3.9926015323784027`*^9, {3.992614805960415*^9, 3.992614812567443*^9}, {
   3.9926154320355377`*^9, 3.99261543850041*^9}, {3.992615560724387*^9, 
   3.992615562136134*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"81edf882-791d-4236-8ed9-\
106a5320e9a7"],

Cell["\<\
where F is the force, r is the lever arm distance, and \[Phi] is the angle \
between the force and lever arm. Assuming F is the gravitational force, namely\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.992097266395308*^9, 3.9920972777812233`*^9}, {
   3.9920974531310387`*^9, 3.992097472807303*^9}, {3.992097745948107*^9, 
   3.9920981476796417`*^9}, {3.992421033765835*^9, 3.992421033879548*^9}, {
